The paper discusses the development of a hybrid language and solver for constraint answer set programming, which involves combining the strengths of answer set programming and constraint programming. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO), as well as programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses algorithmic details and formal claims, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS).
